# Fraud Detection & Risk Monitoring Dashboard

## Overview
This project analyzes financial transaction data to detect fraudulent activity,
monitor risk indicators, and support data-driven decision-making for fraud prevention.

## Business Problem
Financial institutions need visibility into fraud trends across payment channels,
locations, and time periods to reduce financial losses.

## Data Overview
- Transaction amount
- Payment channel
- Location
- Fraud indicator
- Time (Year / Quarter)

## Tools Used
- Power BI
- DAX
- Excel

## Analysis Performed
- Fraud rate calculation
- Channel-level fraud exposure analysis
- Geographic fraud distribution
- Time-based fraud trends

## Key Insights
- Fraud represents a small percentage of total transactions but a disproportionate financial impact
- Certain payment channels show higher fraud concentration
- Fraud activity is clustered in specific regions

## Business Value
This dashboard enables risk teams to prioritize controls,
improve fraud monitoring, and reduce financial exposure.

